# .trivyignore — Justifications for accepted CVEs
# Reviewed: 2026-04-26
#
# Format: One advisory ID per line. Comments starting with # are honored.

# ─── xlsx / SheetJS prototype pollution ─────────────────────────────────────
# CVE: GHSA-4r6h-8v6p-xvw6
# Status: Mitigated, not exploitable in our usage
# Reasoning: We migrated to https://cdn.sheetjs.com/xlsx-0.20.3 (the
#   maintained SheetJS distribution), where this CVE does not apply. Trivy's
#   advisory database still flags any "xlsx" package by name, so we explicitly
#   acknowledge it here. SheetJS docs note: "Snyk is falsely reporting
#   vulnerabilities... the official recommendation is to suppress the warning."
GHSA-4r6h-8v6p-xvw6

# ─── xlsx / SheetJS ReDoS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CVE: GHSA-5pgg-2g8v-p4x9
# Status: Mitigated, not exploitable in our usage
# Reasoning: Same as above. Maintained CDN release (0.20.3) does not expose
#   the regex pattern flagged by this CVE. Authentication-gated upload path
#   limits blast radius even if the legacy issue resurfaced.
GHSA-5pgg-2g8v-p4x9
